&lt;pre&gt;It is a pure UA feature, I was thinking more of cases where websites
anticipate (without getting official confirmation back from the UA) that a
spelling/grammar check was run to assist with users editing text. In
practice, I assume most sites have basic fields that weren't designed to
consider that or are a full text editor like google docs that has its own
spelling/grammar check with no UA dependency.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

